The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Wednesday, July 06, 2005 

 IN THE CITY

 India under-19 cricket captain Manoj Tewari was adjudged the best under-19 cricketer of CAB for the season 2004-05. Ritam Kundu and Rohan Banerjee were jointly chosen the best under-17 cricketers. Sayan Sekhar Mondal in under-15, Subhajit Banerjee in sub-junior and Vinod Kumar Patra in the junior were the others adjudged best players. 

 Bengal fitness trainer Chinmoy Roy has been asked by the Board of Control for Cricket in India (BCCI) to help Team India fitness trainer Greg King in the ongoing camp in Bangalore. Roy received the letter from the BCCI on June 25 and is currently on duty in Bangalore. 

 After being engaged in the Zonal Cricket Academy (East) at Eden Gardens, Roy was called to Team India?s camp along with another trainer from West Zone as the support staff. 

 Roy will be there in Bangalore till July 12. 

 Calcutta Police got the better of La Martiniere Old Boys 39-0 in a Calcutta Cup rugby match at the CC amp;FC on Tuesday. 

 AQUATICS: Third day of 32nd junior national meet at the Subhas Sarobar Pool from 7 am.

 RUGBY: Calcutta Cup at the CC amp;FC from 4.15 pm.




